&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gyffin Receptionist&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A vacancy has arisen within Gyffin Surgery in Conwy for a part time receptionist working 23.25 hours per week over 4 afternoons (days to be confirmed), working with an enthusiastic team just outside Conwy Castle, this renovated Chapel is situated on the Woodlands in Conwy. The Practice is a Health Board run Practice with approximately 4,000 patients with a full compliment of receptionists / administrators and nursing team. We currently have regular locum GPs working in Gyffin but have now received interest for salaried GP positions. This has a warm and friendly atmosphere where you will be made to feel at home.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is essential for this post&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date - 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information, please contact Debbie Searle, Practice Manager email &lt;/span&gt;debbie.searle@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01492 596381&lt;/p&gt;
